                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3208: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Jean de Luz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-19T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 19, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 19—8:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>113. At meeting Diplomatic Corps Friday evening unanimously decided to ignore
                    suggestion concerning Madrid. British, French, Argentine and other nationals
                    with Embassies open there with Chargé <pb facs="0822" n="723" xml:id="pg_723"/>
                    d’ Affaires took position suggestion could not apply to them. Am still convinced
                    it was aimed at Italy, Germany and Portugal, who have closed Embassies in Madrid
                    and moved to Alicante.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
